 in Japan’s imperial project were both a burden and the basis for a new way of life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aConcentration camp inmateszRussia (Federation)zSiberiavBiography. 0aConcentration campszRussia (Federation)zSiberiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aImperialismxSocial aspectszEast AsiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aInternment camp inmateszRussia (Federation)zSiberiavBiography. 0aInternment campszRussia (Federation)zSiberiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aJapanesezEast AsiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aJapanesezRussia (Federation)zSiberiavBiography. 0aJapanesezRussia (Federation)zSiberiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aRepatriationzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  a1945.  aallied bombing campaigns.  aallied forces.  aanthropology.  aasian empire.  aasian history.  acaptivity.  achina.  acontemporary records.  aengaging.  aforced labor.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  aimperial japan.  ajapanese history.  ajapanese imperialism.  akorea.  alabor camps.  amanchuria.  amemoirs.  amen at war.  apage turner.  apoetry.  apolitical.  apostwar japan.  aprimary sources.  ared army.  areeducation camps.  arepatriation.  aretrospective.  asiberia.  awarfare.  awarriors.  aworld war 2.  awwii.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095657540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520956575423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520956575/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles